sec.p:
The primary objective of the study is:
to assess the clinical, genetic and epigenetic features of children with FSHD to optimize clinical management.
The secondary objectives are:
to define a new comprehensive definition of early onset FSHD;
to provide prevalence estimations of early onset FSHD in The Netherlands;
to establish a well-characterized baseline cohort for prospective follow-up and recruitment for future clinical trials;
to assess 2-year disease progression rate in children with FSHD and develop a prognostic model.
